ome patients: MyPlate.gov vs calorie counting. Annals of Family Medicine. 2023;20 (3):1-7."},"publicationIDType":{"typeName":"publicationIDType","multiple":false,"typeClass":"controlledVocabulary","value":"doi"},"publicationIDNumber":{"typeName":"publicationIDNumber","multiple":false,"typeClass":"primitive","value":"doi.org/10.1370/afm.2964"},"publicationURL":{"typeName":"publicationURL","multiple":false,"typeClass":"primitive","value":"https://doi.org/10.1370/afm.2964"}}]},{"typeName":"notesText","multiple":false,"typeClass":"primitive","value":"We conducted a randomized controlled trial comparing the calorie counting (CC) and MyPlate approached from 2015 to 2017. The adult participants were overweight, low income and mostly Hispanic (N = 261 at baseline). For both approaches, community health workers conducted 2 home education visits, 2 group education sessions, and 7 telephone coaching calls over a period of 6 months. Satiation and satiety were the primary patient-centered outcome measures. Waist circumference and body weight were the primary anthropometric measures. Measures were assessed at baseline, 6 months, and 12 months."},{"typeName":"depositor","multiple":false,"typeClass":"primitive","value":"MCCARTHY, WILLIAM"},{"typeName":"dateOfDeposit","multiple":false,"typeClass":"primitive","value":"2023-03-21"}]}},"files":[{"description":"Codebook for final MyPlate survey measures used in McCarthy et al. Annals of Family Med., 2023","label":"Codebook for final PCORI survey data (public use).2023 09 20.txt","restricted":false,"version":1,"datasetVersionId":342829,"dataFile":{"id":7077228,"persistentId":"","filename":"Codebook for final PCORI survey data (public use).2023 09 20.txt","contentType":"text/plain","friendlyType":"Plain Text","filesize":189100,"description":"Codebook for final MyPlate survey measures used in McCarthy et al. Annals of Family Med., 2023","storageIdentifier":"s3://dvn-cloud:187a27f8c4f-397c5246a1a5","rootDataFileId":-1,"md5":"8f697d99d4f221b